Citation.sTitle: Densities and Viscosities of Aqueous Solutions of N-Methylmorpholine from (293.15 to 343.15) K
Citation.sAbstract: The experimental densities, F, and viscosities, c, of aqueous solutions of N-methylmorpholine were measured over the entire composition range at temperatures from (293.15 to 343.15) K and at atmospheric pressure. The excess molar volumes VE and viscosity deviations Ac were calculated from the experimental results of density and viscosity measurements and fitted to the Redlich-Kister polynomial equation. The VE values are negative, while viscosity deviations Ac are positive over the entire composition range and at all temperatures.
